# Stable, hardware-derived representor names. Shipped active by the package
# (installed to /lib/udev/rules.d/).
#
# Give the ConnectX VF representors stable, self-describing names derived from
# hardware (phys_port_name: pf0vf0 .. pf0vf31) instead of the unstable kernel
# eth0..eth31 names. The kernel ethN order is not guaranteed across kernel
# upgrades or added NICs, so a renumber could silently drop a representor out of
# the bridge and black-hole a VM's uplink; the hardware-derived names are stable.
#
# The rename applies on the next boot, when the VFs are (re-)created -- not live,
# so it never renames a representor out from under a running bridge. Your
# bridge-ports in /etc/network/interfaces MUST reference these pf0vfN names (see
# the bundled examples/interfaces.snippet); the package does not manage that
# file. On an existing node whose bridge still pins eth0..eth31, update that line
# before the next reboot or the bridge comes up with no VF ports.

SUBSYSTEM=="net", ACTION=="add", DRIVERS=="mlx5_core", \
    ATTR{phys_switch_id}=="?*", ATTR{phys_port_name}=="pf?vf*", \
    NAME="$attr{phys_port_name}"
